cs.CY, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR

This paper involves the development of a model that identifies distant recurrences in breast cancer using clinical narratives and structured data from EHR. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories:

- cs.CY (Computers and Society): This sub-category deals with the interaction between computing and society, including topics such as healthcare and medical informatics.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): This sub-category deals with natural language processing and text analysis, which are relevant to the feature extraction from clinical narratives in this paper.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): This sub-category deals with the development of machine learning models, which is the main focus of this paper.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): This sub-category deals with the development of intelligent systems, which is relevant to the use of machine learning in this paper.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): This sub-category deals with the security and privacy of data, which is relevant to the use of EHR data in this paper.
